The paper deals with a machine learning classification problem and proposes a new methodology to enhance the robustness of the existing kernel null-space technique. The paper discusses the effect of regularisation on the solution and proposes iterative algorithms to update label confidences and rank training observations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the sensitivity analysis problem, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Systems and Control), and proposes iterative algorithms, which fall under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
